    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1874-09-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1874-09-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="173" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d173">
                <head>No. 171.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Williams</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1874-09-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 12,
                            1874</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 186.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your dispatch of July 7, No. 44,
                        relating to the joint trial at Ohifu of persons who attacked Mr. Corbett, an
                        American missionary <pb facs="0442" n="346" xml:id="pg_346"/> at Chimi, I
                        take pleasure in stating that your course in relation to the matter is
                        regarded by the Department as prudent and fair, and that Mr. Sheppard has
                        the cordial approval of the Department for the firmness and discretion
                        displayed by him in conducting the case.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
